# Users [/users]

User-related endpoints. In WatchWise, most users are created via OAuth. Some endpoints may still be used
to fetch and update the local profile.

## Get My Profile [GET /users/me]

Returns the authenticated user's profile.

+ Request
    + Headers
            Authorization: Bearer <token>

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (User)

## Get User By Id [GET /users/{id}]

+ Parameters
    + id: `663b2f1e9c1d2a001e8e4f1a` (string) - User ID (ObjectId string)

+ Request
    + Headers
            Authorization: Bearer <token>

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (User)

## Update My Profile [PATCH /users/me]

Update username and/or avatar for the authenticated user.

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers
            Authorization: Bearer <token>
    + Attributes (UserUpdate)

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (User)

## Delete My Account [DELETE /users/me]

Deletes the authenticated user and related data (implementation-dependent).

+ Request
    + Headers
            Authorization: Bearer <token>

+ Response 204

