# Preferences [/preferences]

Preferences are stored as **events**. They can come from:
- `explicit`: user manually likes/dislikes genres, actors, directors, etc.
- `questionnaire`: daily/periodic answers that influence the preference profile

The recommendation engine builds a **preference profile** by aggregating events.

## List My Preference Events [GET /preferences/me]

Returns all preference events for the authenticated user.

+ Request
    + Headers
            Authorization: Bearer <token>

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (array[PreferenceEvent])

## Add Preference Event [POST /preferences]

Creates a single preference event.

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers
            Authorization: Bearer <token>
    + Attributes (PreferenceEventCreate)

+ Response 201 (application/json)
    + Attributes (PreferenceEvent)

## Bulk Add Preference Events [POST /preferences/bulk]

Creates multiple preference events in one request.
Useful when the UI saves a whole questionnaire page at once.

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers
            Authorization: Bearer <token>
    + Attributes (PreferenceEventBulkCreate)

+ Response 201 (application/json)
    + Attributes
        + created: (array[PreferenceEvent])

## Delete Preference Event [DELETE /preferences/{id}]

Deletes a single preference event by id.

+ Parameters
    + id: `663b2f1e9c1d2a001e8e4f1a` (string) - Preference event id

+ Request
    + Headers
            Authorization: Bearer <token>

+ Response 204

## Delete Preference Events By Source [DELETE /preferences/source/{source}]

Deletes all preference events of a given source for the authenticated user.
Example: clear all `explicit` likes, or clear all `questionnaire` events.

+ Parameters
    + source: `explicit` (string) - `explicit` or `questionnaire`

+ Request
    + Headers
            Authorization: Bearer <token>

+ Response 204

## Get Group Questionnaire Status [GET /groups/{groupId}/questionnaire-status]

Returns the questionnaire completion status for each member of a group, used as a readiness gate
before group recommendations.

+ Parameters
    + groupId: `663b2f1e9c1d2a001e8e4f1a` (string) - Group ID

+ Request
    + Headers
            Authorization: Bearer <token>

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (GroupQuestionnaireStatus)

